{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2063,"text":"I opened a blind man's head."},{"time":5363,"text":"I didn't make him think or reflect --\nI cracked his head open, literally."},{"time":10564,"text":"We were walking with him\nholding onto my shoulder,"},{"time":12993,"text":"I miscalculated how much space\nthere was between us,"},{"time":15857,"text":"and I knocked him into a gate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17646,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18837,"text":"Five stitches in his forehead."},{"time":21863,"text":"At that moment, I felt like\nthe worst teacher in the world."},{"time":24960,"text":"I really didn't know how to apologize."},{"time":27845,"text":"Luckily, El Pulga is one of those people\nwho takes things quite well."},{"time":34228,"text":"And to this day, he says\nthat I was the coach"},{"time":36776,"text":"who left the most important\nmark on his career."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39244,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":41441,"text":"The truth is, when I started working\nat the institute for the blind,"},{"time":44747,"text":"I was surprised by a lot of things."},{"time":46926,"text":"A lot of the things they did,\nI never imagined they could:"},{"time":50474,"text":"they swam, did exercise, played cards."},{"time":54970,"text":"They drank mate, and could pour it"},{"time":56648,"text":"without burning themselves in the process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58736,"text":"But when I saw them playing soccer --"},{"time":60553,"text":"that was amazing."},{"time":62672,"text":"They had a dirt field,\nrusty goalposts and broken nets."},{"time":67054,"text":"The blind who attended the institute\nwould play their games there,"},{"time":70225,"text":"just like I did at a field near my house."},{"time":72824,"text":"But they played without being able to see."},{"time":75534,"text":"The ball made a sound\nso they could locate it."},{"time":79039,"text":"They had a guide\nbehind the rival team's goal"},{"time":82074,"text":"to know where to kick the ball."},{"time":84102,"text":"And they used eye masks."},{"time":86004,"text":"There were guys\nwho could still see a little,"},{"time":88264,"text":"and they wore eye masks\nso everyone was equal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92524,"text":"When I was more at ease with them,\nI asked for a mask myself."},{"time":97200,"text":"I put it on and tried to play."},{"time":99870,"text":"I had played soccer all my life."},{"time":102272,"text":"This is where it got even more amazing:"},{"time":104342,"text":"within two seconds, I didn't know\nwhere I was standing."},{"time":110126,"text":"I had studied physical education\nbecause I loved high performance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113904,"text":"I started working\nat the institute by chance."},{"time":116143,"text":"My other job was with the Argentinian\nNational Rowing Team,"},{"time":119014,"text":"and I felt that was my thing."},{"time":121262,"text":"Here, everything was twice as hard."},{"time":123785,"text":"I'll never forget the first day\nI did the warm-up with the team."},{"time":127564,"text":"I lined them up in front of me --"},{"time":129300,"text":"I used to do that with the rowing team --"},{"time":132193,"text":"and I said, \"OK, everyone\nbend down,\" going like this."},{"time":135472,"text":"When I looked up, two guys were seated,"},{"time":137438,"text":"three were lying down\nand others were squatting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139771,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":141161,"text":"How could I do here\nthe same things I was doing there?"},{"time":146907,"text":"It took me a while."},{"time":148314,"text":"I started looking for tools\nto learn from them,"},{"time":151802,"text":"from the teachers who worked with them."},{"time":154394,"text":"I learned I couldn't explain a play\non a chalkboard like a coach does,"},{"time":159064,"text":"but I could use a plastic tray\nand some bottle caps"},{"time":161868,"text":"so they could follow me by way of touch."},{"time":164779,"text":"I also learned they could run on a track"},{"time":167956,"text":"if I ran with them, holding a rope."},{"time":170656,"text":"So we started looking for volunteers\nto help us run with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174312,"text":"I was enjoying it,"},{"time":177764,"text":"and finding purpose and meaning\nin what we were doing."},{"time":181805,"text":"It was hard at first,\nit was uncomfortable,"},{"time":183931,"text":"but I decided to overcome the discomfort."},{"time":186098,"text":"And there came a time"},{"time":187544,"text":"when it became the most\nfascinating job I'd ever had."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191249,"text":"I think that's when I wondered:"},{"time":193630,"text":"Why couldn't we be\na high-performance team as well?"},{"time":198966,"text":"Of course, one thing was missing:"},{"time":200723,"text":"I needed to find out what they wanted,"},{"time":202817,"text":"the real protagonists of this story."},{"time":206823,"text":"Three hours of training,\nplaying soccer on that field,"},{"time":210349,"text":"were not going to be enough."},{"time":211984,"text":"We would have to train differently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214143,"text":"We started to train harder,\nand the results were great;"},{"time":217906,"text":"they asked for more."},{"time":219733,"text":"I came to understand\nthat they, too, wondered"},{"time":221879,"text":"why they couldn't do high-performance."},{"time":225151,"text":"When we felt ready,\nwe knocked at CENARD's door."},{"time":229174,"text":"CENARD is the National Center\nfor High-Performance Sports"},{"time":231938,"text":"here in Argentina."},{"time":233306,"text":"It was hard to get them\nto hear what we had to say."},{"time":235747,"text":"But it was considerably more difficult"},{"time":238227,"text":"to get the other athletes training there\nto consider us their equals."},{"time":242662,"text":"In fact, they would let us use the field"},{"time":244622,"text":"only when no other teams were using it."},{"time":247367,"text":"And we were known as \"the blind ones.\""},{"time":249724,"text":"Not everyone knew\nexactly what we were doing there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253622,"text":"The 2006 World Championship\nwas a turning point in the team's history."},{"time":258449,"text":"It was held in Buenos Aires\nfor the first time."},{"time":261257,"text":"It was our chance to show everyone"},{"time":264080,"text":"what we had been doing all that time."},{"time":266947,"text":"We made it to the finals."},{"time":269020,"text":"We were growing as a team."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271374,"text":"It was us against Brazil in the finals."},{"time":274406,"text":"They were the best team in the tournament."},{"time":277033,"text":"They won every game by a landslide."},{"time":280264,"text":"Hardly anyone believed\nwe could win that game."},{"time":285942,"text":"Hardly anyone -- except for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288935,"text":"During pre-game meetings,"},{"time":290833,"text":"in the locker room,"},{"time":292500,"text":"during each warm-up,"},{"time":294592,"text":"it smelled of victory."},{"time":298079,"text":"I swear that smell exists."},{"time":300433,"text":"I smelled it several times with the team,"},{"time":303079,"text":"but I remember it in particular,\nthe day before we played that final."},{"time":307328,"text":"The Argentine Football Association\nhad opened their doors to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310464,"text":"We were training at AFA,"},{"time":311954,"text":"where Ver√≥n, Higuain and Messi trained."},{"time":314472,"text":"For the first time ever,"},{"time":317081,"text":"we felt like a true national team."},{"time":320214,"text":"At 7:30pm, the day before the game,"},{"time":322695,"text":"we were in the lounge discussing strategy,"},{"time":326547,"text":"and a waiter knocks on the door,\ninterrupting our conversation."},{"time":330646,"text":"He suggested we go to church."},{"time":332354,"text":"He came to invite us to church."},{"time":335253,"text":"I tried to get rid of him,\nsaying it wasn't a good time,"},{"time":339139,"text":"that we better leave it for another day."},{"time":341992,"text":"He kept insisting, asking me to please\nlet him take the guys to church,"},{"time":347507,"text":"because that day, a pastor\nwho performed miracles would be there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352400,"text":"I was slightly afraid to ask\nwhat type of miracles he meant,"},{"time":355816,"text":"and he replied nonchalantly,"},{"time":358076,"text":"\"Coach, let me take\nthe team to the church,"},{"time":360300,"text":"and when we return, I guarantee\nthat half of them will be able to see.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":364129,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":368655,"text":"Some of the guys laughed,"},{"time":370125,"text":"but imagine being a blind person\nand someone says that to you."},{"time":373299,"text":"I didn't know what to say."},{"time":374708,"text":"I said nothing; it was an awkward silence."},{"time":377376,"text":"I didn't want to make him feel bad,"},{"time":379144,"text":"because he truly believed\nthis could happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382032,"text":"One of the players saved me,"},{"time":384694,"text":"when he stood up and confidently said,"},{"time":386664,"text":"\"Juan,\" -- that was the kid's name --"},{"time":388572,"text":"Gonza already told you\nit's not the best time to go to church."},{"time":391549,"text":"Besides, let me make this clear:"},{"time":393354,"text":"if we go to that church, and I end up\nbeing able to see when we return,"},{"time":397260,"text":"I will beat you so hard\nif I can't play tomorrow.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":400302,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":402030,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412998,"text":"Juan left, laughing in resignation,"},{"time":416966,"text":"and we continued with our pregame talk."},{"time":419687,"text":"That night when I went to sleep,"},{"time":422604,"text":"I began to dream\nabout the next day's game,"},{"time":425949,"text":"imagining what could happen,\nhow we would play."},{"time":428652,"text":"And that's when I noticed\nthat smell of victory"},{"time":431132,"text":"I mentioned a while ago."},{"time":432806,"text":"And it's because\nat that moment, I thought:"},{"time":434993,"text":"if the other players had the same desire\nas Diego going into the game,"},{"time":440261,"text":"it was impossible for us not to win."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443779,"text":"The next day was going to be wonderful."},{"time":446446,"text":"We got up at 9am, the game was at 7pm,"},{"time":449526,"text":"and we were already eager to play."},{"time":452227,"text":"We left AFA, and the bus was full\nof flags that people had given to us."},{"time":458608,"text":"We were talking about the game,"},{"time":460791,"text":"and we could hear people\nhonking and cheering,"},{"time":463355,"text":"\"Go Murci√©lagos! Today's the day!\nThe final challenge!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":466689,"text":"The guys asked me, \"Do they know us?\nDo they know we're playing?\""},{"time":471134,"text":"Some people followed the bus to CENARD."},{"time":475237,"text":"We arrived and found an amazing scene."},{"time":479247,"text":"In the corridor leading\nfrom the locker room to the game field,"},{"time":482337,"text":"I was walking with Silvio,"},{"time":484313,"text":"who was holding onto my shoulder,\nso I could guide him."},{"time":487425,"text":"Fortunately, there were\nno gates along the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489712,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":490736,"text":"When we reached the field,\nhe asked me about everything."},{"time":493872,"text":"He didn't want to miss a single detail."},{"time":495832,"text":"He said, \"Tell me what you see,\ntell me who's playing the drums.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":499675,"text":"I tried to explain what was happening\nwith as much detail as possible."},{"time":503594,"text":"I told him, \"The stands are packed,\na lot of people couldn't get in,"},{"time":508418,"text":"there are blue and white balloons\nall over the field,"},{"time":511036,"text":"they're opening a giant Argentine flag\nthat covers the entire grandstand.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":515201,"text":"Suddenly, he cuts me off and says,"},{"time":517322,"text":"\"Do you see a flag that says 'San Pedro'?\""},{"time":522674,"text":"That's the city where he lives."},{"time":524641,"text":"I started looking into the stands"},{"time":526480,"text":"and I spotted a little white flag"},{"time":529013,"text":"with lettering done\nin black spray paint, that read:"},{"time":532087,"text":"\"Silvio, your family\nand all of San Pedro are here.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":536227,"text":"I told him that and he replied,"},{"time":538983,"text":"\"That's my mom, tell me where\nshe is, I want to I wave at her.\""},{"time":543564,"text":"I pointed him toward the flag"},{"time":545020,"text":"and showed him with his arm\nwhere they were sitting,"},{"time":547590,"text":"and he waved his arms in that direction."},{"time":549598,"text":"About 20 or 30 people stood up\nand gave him an ovation."},{"time":553341,"text":"When that happened,"},{"time":554754,"text":"I saw how his face changed,\nhow moved he was."},{"time":557615,"text":"It was moving for me, too;"},{"time":560106,"text":"two seconds later,\nI had a lump in my throat."},{"time":563318,"text":"It was strange -- I felt both\nthe excitement of what was happening,"},{"time":566628,"text":"and the anger and the anguish\nthat he could not see it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571457,"text":"A few days later when I told him\nwhat I had experienced,"},{"time":577266,"text":"he tried to reassure me, saying,"},{"time":580534,"text":"\"Gonza, don't feel bad, I could see them."},{"time":583135,"text":"Differently, but I swear to you\nthat I saw them all.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":587248,"text":"The game started."},{"time":588668,"text":"We could not fail; it was the final."},{"time":591530,"text":"The audience was quiet, like here,"},{"time":593979,"text":"because in soccer for the blind,"},{"time":595647,"text":"the public has to be quiet\nso the players can hear the ball."},{"time":599064,"text":"They're only allowed to cheer\nwhen the game is over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602265,"text":"And when there were eight minutes to go,"},{"time":605747,"text":"the crowd did all the cheering\nthey hadn't done in the first 32 minutes."},{"time":609218,"text":"When pigeon-toed Silvio\nnailed the ball at an angle,"},{"time":612871,"text":"they cheered with all their heart,"},{"time":614983,"text":"in an incredible way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618848,"text":"Today, if you go to CENARD,\nyou'll see a huge poster on the door,"},{"time":623490,"text":"with a photo of our team,\nLos Murci√©lagos."},{"time":626227,"text":"They're a model national team,\neveryone in CENARD knows who they are,"},{"time":630895,"text":"and after having won\ntwo World Championships"},{"time":633502,"text":"and two Paralympic medals,"},{"time":634923,"text":"no one doubts they are\nhigh-performance athletes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637406,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":652001,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":655148,"text":"I was lucky to train\nthis team for 10 years,"},{"time":658860,"text":"first as a trainer\nand later as their coach."},{"time":663110,"text":"I feel that they've given me much more"},{"time":667993,"text":"than what I've given them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670209,"text":"Last year, they asked me to coach\nanother national team, Power Soccer."},{"time":677394,"text":"It's a national team of young men\nwho play soccer in wheelchairs."},{"time":681824,"text":"They use motorized wheelchairs\nthat they drive with a joystick,"},{"time":684895,"text":"because they don't have\nenough strength in their arms"},{"time":687477,"text":"to use conventional chairs."},{"time":688794,"text":"They added a bumper to the chair,\na safeguard that protects their feet,"},{"time":692528,"text":"while allowing them to kick the ball."},{"time":695548,"text":"It's the first time that, instead\nof being the spectators,"},{"time":699739,"text":"they're now the main characters."},{"time":701580,"text":"It's the first time their parents,\nfriends and siblings can see them play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707760,"text":"For me, it's a new challenge,"},{"time":710127,"text":"with the same discomfort,\ninsecurity, and fear I had"},{"time":713395,"text":"when I started working with the blind."},{"time":715860,"text":"But I approach it all\nfrom a more experienced position."},{"time":718601,"text":"That's why from day one,\nI treat them as athletes on the field,"},{"time":723827,"text":"and off the field, I try\nto put myself in their shoes"},{"time":726461,"text":"and behave without prejudice,"},{"time":727912,"text":"because treating them naturally\nfeels best to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733326,"text":"Both teams play soccer;\nsomething once unthinkable for them."},{"time":738303,"text":"They had to adapt the rules to do so."},{"time":743129,"text":"And both teams broke the same rule --"},{"time":745677,"text":"the one that said\nthey couldn't play soccer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749589,"text":"When you see them play,\nyou see competition, not disability."},{"time":754568,"text":"The problem starts when the game is over,"},{"time":757746,"text":"and they leave the field."},{"time":759245,"text":"Then they step in to play our game,"},{"time":761765,"text":"in a society whose rules\ndon't really take them into account"},{"time":765743,"text":"or care for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767520,"text":"I learned from sports"},{"time":769364,"text":"that disability greatly depends on\nthe rules of the game."},{"time":773512,"text":"I believe that if we change\nsome of the rules of our game,"},{"time":777600,"text":"we can make life a little easier for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781209,"text":"We all know there are people\nwith disabilities; we see them daily."},{"time":786644,"text":"But by having no direct contact with them,"},{"time":789629,"text":"we're not aware of the problems\nthey face every day,"},{"time":793203,"text":"like how hard it is for them\nto get on a bus,"},{"time":795334,"text":"find a job,"},{"time":797009,"text":"take the subway"},{"time":798186,"text":"or cross the street."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800367,"text":"It's true that there is an increasing\nsocial responsibility"},{"time":803562,"text":"regarding the inclusion\nof people with disabilities."},{"time":808466,"text":"But I think it's still not enough."},{"time":810983,"text":"I think change needs to come\nfrom every one of us."},{"time":814046,"text":"First, by leaving behind\nour indifference toward the disabled,"},{"time":817716,"text":"and then by respecting the rules\nthat do take them into account."},{"time":821091,"text":"They are few, but they do exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825158,"text":"I cracked a blind man's head\nopen -- El Pulga's head."},{"time":828669,"text":"I can assure you these two teams\nopened mine as well."},{"time":832547,"text":"They taught me that above all,"},{"time":834008,"text":"you have to get out there\nand play every game"},{"time":836156,"text":"in this beautiful tournament\nthat we call life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838410,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839590,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}